     Examiner Training Program
   Regulations & Examination: Examiner Training Program
     __________________________________________________________________


   a classroom of students sitting at computers The Federal Financial
   Institutions Examination Council (FFIEC) and the FDIC conduct training
   programs for both federal and state examiners.

   FFIEC Examiner Education Office

   The Federal Financial Institutions Examination Council's (FFIEC)
   Examiner Education Office provides training for examiners from the five
   financial institution regulatory agencies that comprise the Council and
   risk-management planning seminars for bankers.

   FDIC Examiner Education Program

     Safety & Soundness Training

     Descriptions of courses that teach FDIC staff to examine banks and
     savings institutions for safety and soundness.
